CNCP v1 23279
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#8517: withDefaults should work with an object literal reference",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:24:20.829021+00:00",
  "text": "withDefaults should work with an object literal reference\n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\n\nCurrently this does not work in my code: \r\n```\r\nconst defaultsObject = {  name: \"Evan You\" }\r\n// also: var defaultsObject = {  name: \"Evan You\" }\r\n// also: let defaultsObject = {  name: \"Evan You\" }\r\n\r\nconst props = withDefaults(defineProps<{name: string}>(), defaultsObject)\r\n```\r\nThis gives the following error:  `The 2nd argument of withDefaults must be an object literal.`\r\n\r\nThere is a good change I am just doing something wrong, if not: \r\n\r\nSince we can now [use interfaces for the props](https://github.com/vuejs/core/issues/4294) it would be really nice to be able to pass an object to the defaults, it was also [a suggestion on the topic](https://github.com/vuejs/core/issues/4294#issuecomment-1005800706) The added value is having the defaults also shared through composables if they are the same in different components. \r\n\n\n### What does the proposed API look like?\n\n```\r\nimport { inputPropertiesInterface, inputDefaultsObject } from '../common/Input';\r\n\r\nconst props = withDefaults(defineProps<inputPropertiesInterface>(), inputDefaultsObject)\r\n```",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request",
    "scope: compiler",
    ":cake: p2-nice-to-have",
    "scope: script-setup"
  ],
